gomodel:SYNGO_3989  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Subcellular fractionation of rat brain indicates the presence of RalA in synaptosomes and synaptic membrane fractions.\n\n18/01/2021 Dnyanada: The paper demonstrates the presence of RalA in PSD fractions (Fig S2F), however, the term \"postsynaptic density\" was not chosen due to\na decrease in signal intensity observed as the fractions become PSD specific (Fig S2G; contrary to the pattern elicited by PSD95). The additional literature cited lie in favour that RalA is indeed a synaptic protein. Figure S2F shows enrichment of RalA in the synaptic membrane fraction (LP1) and was used as the basis for the ontology term.\nFigure 9C-D shows specificity of anti-RalA antibody by a reduced signal in RalA-/- brain extracts.. Experimental description: Figure Legend to Fig S2F: Distribution of RalBP1 and RalA in subcellular fractions of rat brains at P21 and 6 wk." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5615-1014" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-18" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3989" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

dc:contributor  a  owl:AnnotationProperty .
